          <date>1998</date>
          <biblScope type="page" from="226" to="228"/>
          <note>There is sound evidence to support the meaning of spãtion / spãyion in the Egyptian documents as a &amp;quot;wineskin&amp;quot; or as a &amp;quot;skin (of wine, oil, or fish sauce)&amp;quot;. It is possible that spãtion / spãyion was introduced into Egypt by the merchants who frequented the Palestinian wine producing centers of Gaza and Ascalon. &lt;spation, spathion&gt;</note>
        </bibl>
